  fishName: Sinarapan
  scientificName: Mistichthys luzonensis
  description: The world's smallest commercial fish, measuring only 1.2-1.4 cm. Endemic
    to Lake Buhi in Camarines Sur. Known locally as 'tabios'.
  status: 1
  iucnStatus: Endangered
  populationTrend: Decreasing
  habitat: Freshwater lake (Lake Buhi, Camarines Sur)
  distribution: Endemic to Lake Buhi and nearby lakes in Bicol Region, Philippines
  threats: Habitat destruction, water pollution, introduction of predatory fish species,
    siltation, climate change affecting water levels
  importance: World's smallest commercial fish, unique Philippine endemic species,
    important for local economy and culture, indicator species for lake health
  conservationEfforts: Lake protection programs, fishing regulations, habitat restoration,
    community education, research on breeding and conservation
